themes: valuing foundational organizations as community elders
concern about exclusion based on longevity
essential services and spaces provided by foundational organizations
key_phrases: foundational organizations should be considered like the elders in our community
they have experience, wisdom and they are willing to share it for the greater good
they should compete for funding on par with other arts organizations
they should not be excluded just because they've been around for awhile
foundational companies provide space and services to the arts community that are essential
barriers_identified: exclusion of foundational organizations due to longevity
solutions_proposed: allow foundational organizations to compete for funding on par with other arts organizations
do not exclude organizations from funding because of their long-standing presence
